  "notes": [
    "Install the exhaust camshaft sprocket.\n Check that the\nTDC reference points line up.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nChain link (1) to EXH marking (2) on the exhaust camshaft\nsprocket\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nRotate the exhaust camshaft by the hexagon until the exhaust\ncamshaft sprocket is seated in the guide.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nUse a new bolt.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nHold the camshaft by the hexagon.\n \n\n\n\n–\nTightening torque 85 Nm + 30° +\n15° \n \n\n\n\n\n\n–\nDetach the cable ties from the intake camshaft sprocket.",
    "Attach KM-6148 .\n In this position\nthe cams (1) and (2) of cylinder no. 4 point upwards.\n \n\n\n\n•  \nAttach KM-6148 with the enclosed\nbolts (4).\n \n\n\n\n\n\n•  \nSlide the positioning bolts (5) into the designated bores (3)\non the camshaft sprockets.",
    "Release the camshaft timing chain tensioner by pressing on the\ntensioner rail or the camshaft timing chain (using a blunt tool\n– e.g. a smooth–edged assembly lever).\n If the TDC\nmarkings no longer line up with the coloured chain links, refit the\ncamshaft timing chain. Once the crankshaft has been rotated another\nturn they will no longer line up.",
    "Use new gaskets.\n The sealing lips\nof the seals (1) must be inserted into the groove on the cylinder\nhead cover.\n \n\n\n\n–\nTightening torque 9 Nm"
  ]
